creator: Public Information App
descriptionHtml:
NDIS Australia Link is a free app with a clean interface to quickly access NDIS related information in no time. This app is very handy for participants, participant families, service providers, provider staff, and job seekers.

For Participants and Family:
This section help participant and their family to get started with NDIS, it covers links related to process, planning and support.
1. Check Eligibility
Basic eligibility checklist about participants' demography and support needs.
2. How to Apply
A process on how to get started with NDIS and whom to contact.
3. Live Chat
Live interactive chat with NDIS staff at your fingertip.
4. Service Booking
Manage your services like new bookings, change or cancel your service bookings.
5. Find Service Provider in Your Area
Quickly find who is providing desired services in your area.
6. Complaints and Feedbacks
Contact detail to raise your concern or observation about the service delivery quality.
7. State-wise NDIS
NDIS related update specific to NSW, Victoria, Queensland, ACT, Northern Territory, SA, WA, and Tasmania
8. News related to NDIS
Provides latest news and updates for participants and families.

For Providers:
NDIS provider many opportunities to individual, companies, and organizations to get involved with its mission. Here you get information related to onboarding, execution, and maintenance of contracts.
1. Provider Readiness Checklist
Links to a list of requirements to become a registered provider.
2. NDIS Acts and Rules
Australian government rules and regulations.
3. Services Funded by NDIS
List of services funded through NDIS schemes.
4. Check Eligibility
Detail eligibility checklist for providers.
5. Register as a Provider
List for online registration.
6. Service Price Guide
Links on how to calculated various support and service prices.
7. Pricing Updates
Updates about changes in service prices.
8. Quality and Safeguard Commission
List to NDIS Commission page
9. Worker Screening
Requirement and process of worker screening.
10. Complaints and Feedback
Contact details for complaints and feedback.
11. PRODA Login
Service provider login page to plan and execute approved services.

For Job Seekers:
There are regular job openings in different areas of specialization within the NDIS ecosystem. Potential candidates can check and apply to a relevant job in this section.
1. Job List
This provides a list of jobs across the NDIS provider ecosystem.
2. Job Search
Here you can find jobs specific to your area of expertise or your preferred location.
3. NDIS Commission Jobs
This lists officer category jobs in the NDIS Commission itself.
4. Job Alert
The place to set alerts for your desired job so that you get notifications as and when there is a new job.
5. Graduate Program
Covers job openings pertaining to the graduate program.

Disclaimer: WE ARE NOT ASSOCIATED WITH NDIS AUSTRALIA IN ANY FORM. THIS APP PROVIDES INFORMATION RELATED TO NDIS (National Disability Insurance Scheme), NDIS COMMISSION, AND NDIA (National Disability Insurance Agency) AVAILABLE IN PUBLIC DOMAIN FROM FOLLOWING SOURCES.
1. ndis.gov.au
2. ndiscommission.gov.au
3. health.gov.au
4. myplace.ndis.gov.au
